\begin_inset Formula $z_{t}=z_{1t}+z_{2t}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{it}\sim^{iid}U\left[0,\frac{1}{4}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 Given these assumptions, what level of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{1t}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
This will generalize to player 2.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset

 will sustain cooperation when both players are playing a grim trigger strategy?
 Let's further assume that at the beginning of period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

, each player 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 learns 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{it}$
\end_inset

, but only knows the distribution of the other player's probability of ending
 the game.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
What is the expected discount factor at period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

? 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]=\mathbb{E}\left[1-z_{t}\right]=1-\mathbb{E}\left[z_{1t}\right]-\mathbb{E}\left[z_{2t}\right]=1-\frac{1}{4}=\frac{3}{4}.\]

\end_inset

This is also the probability that the game does not end at period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For each player what is the expected probability of the game ending given
 player 1's own draw of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{1t}$
\end_inset

? In other words, what is the expected discount factor
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\mathbb{E}\left[z_{t}|z_{1t}\right]=z_{1t}+\mathbb{E}\left[z_{2t}|z_{1t}\right]=z_{1t}+\mathbb{E}\left[z_{2t}\right]=z_{1t}+\frac{1}{8}\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\therefore\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]=\mathbb{E}\left[1-z_{t}|z_{1t}\right]=1-\mathbb{E}\left[z_{t}|z_{1t}\right]=\frac{7}{8}-z_{1t}\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The payoff for player 1 (and player 2) under the strategy profile above
 starting at any time period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 is: 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
U_{1}(s_{1},s_{2}|z_{1t}) & = & 3+3\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]+3\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]+3\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]^{2}+...\\
 & = & 3+\frac{3\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]}{1-\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]}=3+\frac{3\left(\frac{7}{8}-z_{1t}\right)}{\frac{1}{4}}\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Now let's consider the payoff of player 1, if she decides to deviate in
 period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
U_{1}(s_{1}^{dev},s_{2}|z_{1t}) & = & 5+1\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]+1\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]+1\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]\cdot\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]^{2}+...\\
 & = & 5+\frac{\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}|z_{1t}\right]}{1-\mathbb{E}\left[\delta_{t}\right]}=5+\frac{\left(\frac{7}{8}-z_{1t}\right)}{\frac{1}{4}}\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Therefore, cooperation is sustainable if:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
3+\frac{3\left(\frac{7}{8}-z_{1t}\right)}{\frac{1}{4}}\geq5+\frac{\left(\frac{7}{8}-z_{1t}\right)}{\frac{1}{4}}\Rightarrow z_{1t}\leq\frac{5}{8}\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
But what did we say about the initial distribution? 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{it}\sim^{iid}U\left[0,\frac{1}{4}\right]$
\end_inset

.
